revisions.description: V01.01.21 - Add zhoneVdsl Add efmOamMIB from ZOI 89562 Add efmCuMIB from ZOI 89562
V01.01.19 - Added a new entry for pktcIetfSigMib
V01.01.14 - Added zhoneExperimental branch for Sonet APS.
V01.01.13 - Add Bridge group under communication protocols.
V01.01.01 - Added zhoneRegWtn for registration of Zhone Wireless Transport Node. Added zhoneWtx for RF interfaces on Zhone Wireless Transport Node.
V01.01.02 - Added zhoneSonet for Zhone SONET MIB used for Sechtor 100 and BAN products.
V01.01.03 - Added sechtor100 under zhoneSechtor for Sechtor 100 MIB.
V01.01.04 - Added zhonePpp under zhoneCommunicationProtocols for the PPP MIBs.
V01.01.05 - Add Ds3 Medium Extension Table.
V01.01.07 - Make wireless component names uniformly wtn and radio.
V01.01.11 - Add zhoneZAP object to zhoneGeneric structure.
V01.01.12 - Add sechtor300 group under sechtor

zhone.description: This is the Zhone Information MIB for all entries that are used across all Zhone platforms.

zhoneRegistrations.name: zhoneRegistrations
zhoneRegistrations.description: Sub-tree for registrations. See the Zhone registrations MIB for the actual tree.

zhoneRegMalc.name: zhoneRegMalc
zhoneRegMalc.description: Multiple Access Loop Concentrator product registrations

zhoneProduct.name: zhoneProduct
zhoneProduct.description: Products hierarchy for the Zhone enterprise

zhoneWtn.name: zhoneWtn
zhoneWtn.description: Wireless Transport product specific MIB hierarchy.

zhoneMalc.name: zhoneMalc
zhoneMalc.description: Multiple Access Loop Concentrator product specific MIB hierarchy.

zhoneGeneric.name: zhoneGeneric
zhoneGeneric.description: This hierarchy defines MIB entities for system level information as opposed to information valid only on a specific card type or protocol. MIBs in this hierarchy may or may not be implemented on a specific Zhone platform but are not specific to only one product. Those MIBs will be in the Zhone product MIB hierarchy.

zhoneSystem.name: zhoneSystem
zhoneSystem.description: Zhone parameters that apply to the complete system as opposed to just one card. This augments the standard system MIB.

zhoneShelf.name: zhoneShelf
zhoneShelf.description: The Zhone Shelf MIB contains information specific to a single shelf.

zhoneCard.name: zhoneCard
zhoneCard.description: The Zhone unit MIB containing generic information for a card based entity. This would cover cards in the case of the BAN and a system in the case of single cpu systems.

zhoneSubscriber.name: zhoneSubscriber
zhoneSubscriber.description: Subscriber information. This contains all data associated with a subscriber instance. It will contain voice, data, and video information.

zhoneInterfaceTranslation.name: zhoneInterfaceTranslation
zhoneInterfaceTranslation.description: The interface translation MIB is the Zhone specific mapping of a physical interface to an ifTable entry and vice versa.

zhoneInterfaceGroup.name: zhoneInterfaceGroup
zhoneInterfaceGroup.description: The Interface Group is the Zhone specific mapping of two lines to a common group. The group represents their primary/secondary relationship and determines their group behavior during line switching due to failure or maintainance operations.

zhoneTrapModules.name: zhoneTrapModules
zhoneTrapModules.description: This provides a grouping for miscellaneous Traps. This space should only be used by modules that don't have a MIB associated with them.

zhoneGenWtn.name: zhoneGenWtn
zhoneGenWtn.description: Zhone Wireless Transport generic Mib group.

zhoneZAP.name: zhoneZAP
zhoneZAP.description: Zhone Wireless Transport generic Mib group.

zhoneVoiceStats.name: zhoneVoiceStats
zhoneVoiceStats.description: Voice Call Statistics. This Object contains all instances associated with voice calls statistics.

zhoneSFF.name: zhoneSFF
zhoneSFF.description: Small Form Factor (SFF) Pluggable and Fixed for both 1Gb (SFP) and 10Gb (XFP) modules.

zhoneInterfaceConfig.name: zhoneInterfaceConfig
zhoneInterfaceConfig.description: The Zhone Interface Config table is a mechanism to be able to configure a group of physical ifIndex to the same parameters.

zhoneCommunicationProtocols.name: zhoneCommunicationProtocols
zhoneCommunicationProtocols.description: This MIB hierarchy defines the communication protocol specific MIBs (e.g. IP) that are Zhone proprietary. They may or may not be implemented on a specific Zhone product based upon what functionality is supported on that product.

zhoneVoip.name: zhoneVoip
zhoneVoip.description: Voice over IP related Zhone MIBs.

zhoneCes.name: zhoneCes
zhoneCes.description: Circuit Emulation Service related (CES) Zhone MIBs.

zhoneBonding.name: zhoneBonding
zhoneBonding.description: Zhone Bonding protocols, including EFM, N2N and MLPPP.

zhoneRadius.name: zhoneRadius
zhoneRadius.description: Zhone RADIUS protocols including both client and server.

zhonePtp.name: zhonePtp
zhonePtp.description: MIB elements for Zhone's implementation of the IEEE Precision Timing Protocol.

zhonePhysical.name: zhonePhysical
zhonePhysical.description: This MIB hierarchy contains Zhone proprietary MIBs for implementing different physical interfaces.

zhoneConsole.name: zhoneConsole
zhoneConsole.description: Zhone MIBs required for implementing the console interface. The RS-232 MIB was not implemented due to the fact this was much more complex than what was required for this simple interface.

zhoneRadio.name: zhoneRadio
zhoneRadio.description: Zhone MIBs for radio interfaces used in the Zhone Wireless Transport Node.

zhoneSonet.name: zhoneSonet
zhoneSonet.description: Zhone SONET MIB used in the Zhone Sechtor 100 and BAN products.

zhoneDs3Ext.name: zhoneDs3Ext
zhoneDs3Ext.description: Zhone Ds3Ext MIB used in the Zhone BAN product.

zhoneLineTypes.name: zhoneLineTypes
zhoneLineTypes.description: Zhone custom physical line and port configurations.

zhoneWdm.name: zhoneWdm
zhoneWdm.description: Wave Division Multiplexing related Zhone MIBs.

zhoneCpe.name: zhoneCpe
zhoneCpe.description: CPE profiles for Voip and Pseudo wire.

zhoneShelfSlotTable.name: zhoneShelfSlotTable
zhoneShelfSlotTable.description: The shelf/slot table is included to provide the table entries zhoneShelfIndex and zhoneSlotIndex allowing these indexes to be imported and used globally.

zhoneShelfSlotEntry.name: zhoneShelfSlotEntry
zhoneShelfSlotEntry.description: Entry for the shelf/slot index table.

zhoneShelfIndex.name: zhoneShelfIndex
zhoneShelfIndex.description: The global shelf index. This index can be used by tables that index by shelf and slot eliminating the need for shelf and slot columns in the table.

zhoneSlotIndex.name: zhoneSlotIndex
zhoneSlotIndex.description: The global slot index. This index can be used by tables that index by shelf and slot eliminating the need to include shelf and slot columns in the table.

zhoneShelfSlotGroup.name: zhoneShelfSlotGroup
zhoneShelfSlotGroup.description: Group which contains the standard objects for addressing shelf and slot values on Zhone products

zhoneShelfSlotCompliance.name: zhoneShelfSlotCompliance
zhoneShelfSlotCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage Zhone Devices.

ietfDrafts.name: ietfDrafts
ietfDrafts.description: IETF Draft Mibs currently under review.

apsMIB.name: apsMIB
apsMIB.description: SONET Linear APS architectures taken from draft-ietf-atommib-sonetaps-mib-05.txt.

sipTC.name: sipTC
sipTC.description: SIP (Session Initiated Protocol) taken from draft-ietf-sip-mib-05.txt.

sipCommonMIB.name: sipCommonMIB
sipCommonMIB.description: SIP (Session Initiated Protocol) taken from draft-ietf-sip-mib-05.txt.

sipUAMIB.name: sipUAMIB
sipUAMIB.description: SIP (Session Initiated Protocol) taken from draft-ietf-sip-mib-05.txt.

pktcIetfSigMib.name: pktcIetfSigMib
pktcIetfSigMib.description: Endpoint signaling mib taken from draft-ietf-ipcdn-signaling-06.txt.

efmOamMIB.name: efmOamMIB
efmOamMIB.description: EFM Oam mib taken from draft-ietf-hubmib-efm-mib-03.txt.

efmCuMIB.name: efmCuMIB
efmCuMIB.description: EFM Cu mib taken from draft-ietf-hubmib-efm-mib-04.txt.

pwTcStdMIB.name: pwTcStdMIB
pwTcStdMIB.description: This MIB module defines TEXTUAL CONVENTIONs for concepts used in Pseudo Wire Edge-to-Edge networks.

ianaPwe3MIB.name: ianaPwe3MIB
ianaPwe3MIB.description: This MIB module defines the IANAPwTypeTC and IANAPwPsnTypeTC textual conventions for use in PWE3 MIB modules.

pwStdMIB.name: pwStdMIB
pwStdMIB.description: This MIB module contains managed object definitions for pseudowire operation as in Bryant, S. and P. Pate, 'Pseudo Wire Emulation Edge-to-Edge (PWE3) Architecture' [RFC3985].

pwTDMMIB.name: pwTDMMIB
pwTDMMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for encapsulating TDM (T1,E1, T3, E3, NxDS0) as pseudo-wires over packet-switching networks (PSN).

zhoneRmonMibModule.name: zhoneRmonMibModule
zhoneRmonMibModule.description: This MIB contains objects similar to rfc2819 RMON-2. The etherStatsEntry index has been modified to be an ifIndex value. There is also added support for various Broadcom supported stats.
